# AWS EC2 Quiz Challenge

This repository contains a quiz application that you'll run on an AWS EC2 instance. Follow the instructions below to set up the environment, run the quiz, and clean up your resources.

## Instructions

### 1. Launch an EC2 Instance

1. Log in to your AWS Management Console.
2. Navigate to the EC2 dashboard.
3. Click "Launch Instance".
4. Choose an Amazon Linux 2 AMI.
5. Select a t2.micro instance type (free tier eligible).
6. Configure instance details as needed.
7. Add storage (default is usually fine).
8. Add tags if desired.
9. Configure security group:
   - Allow SSH (port 22) from your IP.
   - Allow HTTP (port 80) from anywhere.
10. Review and launch the instance.
11. Create or select an existing key pair and launch the instance.

### 2. Answer the Quiz

- Complete the quiz questions presented in your web browser.
- Submit your answers when finished.

### 6. Terminate the EC2 Instance

After completing the quiz:

1. Return to the AWS Management Console.
2. Go to the EC2 dashboard.
3. Select your instance.
4. Click "Instance State" > "Terminate Instance".
5. Confirm the termination.

## Important Notes

- Remember to always terminate your EC2 instance when you're done to avoid unnecessary charges.
- Make sure to remove any sensitive information (like access keys) before pushing code to this repository.
- This setup is for educational purposes and may not be suitable for production environments without further security measures.

Good luck with the quiz!